00:02:58.880 --> 00:03:02.460
And then I realized I wasn't
going to learn anything new.

00:03:02.460 --> 00:03:05.510
I had to let go of
my expectations,

00:03:05.510 --> 00:03:10.040
the idealistic view I had
of the world, my mentality

00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:12.410
to blame everybody
else except for myself

00:03:12.410 --> 00:03:14.747
for my problems and
my circumstances.

00:03:14.747 --> 00:03:16.580
And when I began letting
go of these things,

00:03:16.580 --> 00:03:18.320
I started feeling lighter.

00:03:18.320 --> 00:03:22.250
And as I felt lighter, I
was able to take a bigger

00:03:22.250 --> 00:03:26.008
journey inside myself,
learn who I was,

00:03:26.008 --> 00:03:27.550
because they always
said be yourself,

00:03:27.550 --> 00:03:30.090
but you can't be yourself
if you don't know yourself.

00:03:30.090 --> 00:03:32.250
So as I got to
know myself better,

00:03:32.250 --> 00:03:35.240
I was able to live a more
authentic life, which

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:37.990
often, people refer to as
their best life, right?

00:03:37.990 --> 00:03:40.220
So from that
perspective, I think

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:42.560
it's important to kind of
let go more than we gain.

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:44.745
And I mean, society,
consumerism, everything,

00:03:44.745 --> 00:03:46.370
it teaches us you
have to acquire more.

00:03:46.370 --> 00:03:48.810
You need more, and more, and
more, and more to be better.

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:50.840
But I think the reality
is, we really need

00:03:50.840 --> 00:03:52.310
to be polishing things off.

00:03:52.310 --> 00:03:55.130
We need to grab
some big sandpaper

00:03:55.130 --> 00:03:57.440
and get rid of all this
rust because a lot of this

00:03:57.440 --> 00:03:58.730
is formed over the years.

00:03:58.730 --> 00:04:00.594
