00:46:07.340 --> 00:46:09.418
And then once I got
a little bit older,

00:46:09.418 --> 00:46:11.585
and started meeting people
from other neighborhoods,

00:46:11.585 --> 00:46:15.390
and realizing that I was
considered crass or rude,

00:46:15.390 --> 00:46:17.030
and not feeling
that I was myself.

00:46:17.030 --> 00:46:22.400
I felt I was just a direct
communicator and feeling

00:46:22.400 --> 00:46:25.550
that it's OK for there to
be a little bit of conflict.

00:46:25.550 --> 00:46:28.400
It's OK for there to be
a little bit of friction

00:46:28.400 --> 00:46:31.190
because from that,
a lot can grow.

00:46:31.190 --> 00:46:37.910
We, as a species, are safer
now than we've ever been.

00:46:37.910 --> 00:46:41.780
But we're more sensitive
to negative news

00:46:41.780 --> 00:46:42.840
and negative violence.

00:46:42.840 --> 00:46:45.110
And I think that we
might be doing ourselves

00:46:45.110 --> 00:46:46.390
a disservice because of that.

00:46:46.390 --> 00:46:49.520
And so for me and my
